A health worker in Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) suit collects a swab sample from a man to test for the COVID-19 coronavirus at the department of medical research (DMR) in Yangon on October 8, 2020. Ye Aung Thu / AFP JOHANNESBURG - The country has recorded 7,882 new COVID-19 infections over the past 24 hours. This brings the total number of confirmed coronavirus cases in the country to 852,965. The Department of Health has reported 154 new COVID-19 related deaths in South Africa, pushing the death toll to 23,106. READ: 948 pupils test positive for COVID-19 after Rage event The Eastern Cape still accounts for most of the new COVID-19 deaths. Over 760,000 people have recovered from the virus, meaning the country is dealing with just under 70,000 active cases.